  "prompt": "I have an aversion to shaking hands with strangers. How can I avoid this and not be rude?",
  "response": "Here are some polite ways to avoid shaking hands:\n\n1. Use verbal greetings\n- A warm \"Hello\" or \"Nice to meet you\"\n- Use a friendly tone and smile\n\n2. Cultural alternatives\n- Slight bow\n- Hand over heart\n- Wave\n- Nod\n\n3. Pre-emptive strategies\n- Keep hands occupied (holding something)\n- Cross arms or have hands in pockets\n\n4. Explain if needed\n- \"I prefer not to shake hands\"\n- \"I'm currently trying to avoid physical contact\"\n\n5. During pandemic/health concerns\n- Many people are more understanding about avoiding physical contact\n\n6. Professional settings\n- If crucial, briefly explain personal preference\n- Most people will understand if you're respectful\n\nTips:\n- Be confident\n- Maintain eye contact\n- Smile warmly\n- Use a friendly tone\n- Don't apologize extensively\n\nRemember, your comfort and health boundaries are valid. Most people will respect a polite, direct approach.",
